ZH: 我买了一把钉子。
EN: I bought a bundle of nails.

ZH: 请把钉子钉在木板上。
EN: Please nail the nails onto the wooden board.

ZH: 钉子是用来连接两块木料的。
EN: Nails are used to connect two pieces of wood together.

ZH: 他把钉子放在工具箱里。
EN: He puts the nails in the toolbox.

ZH: 这些钉子很尖啊。
EN: These nails are sharp.

ZH: 把这块木板固定好需要很多钉子。
EN: It takes a lot of nails to secure this wooden board properly.

ZH: 昨天我踩到了一根钉子。
EN: I stepped on a nail yesterday.

ZH: 小心别让钉子刺伤你的手。
EN: Be careful not to let the nail prick your hand.

ZH: 我需要一把锤子和一些钉子。
EN: I need a hammer and some nails.

ZH: 这根钉子有点生锈了。
EN: This nail is a bit rusty.

ZH: 他掉了一根钉子，所以他找不到了。
EN: He dropped a nail, so he couldn't find it.

ZH: 这些钉子都是用不锈钢制造的。
EN: These nails are all made of stainless steel.

ZH: 请小心，钉子很容易伤到手指。
EN: Please be careful, nails can easily hurt your fingers.

ZH: 到底上哪里钉这根钉子？
EN: Where exactly should I nail this nail?

ZH: 钉子在箱子底部。
EN: The nails are at the bottom of the box.

ZH: 她的鞋底被钉子扎破了。
EN: Her shoe sole was pierced by a nail.

ZH: 他很快就用了一盒钉子。
EN: He quickly used up a box of nails.

ZH: 这块木板需要很多钉子来固定。
EN: This wooden board needs a lot of nails to secure it.

ZH: 他使用了自动铆钉机来固定金属结构。
EN: He used an automatic nail gun to secure the metal structure.
